FBIS3-37109 "drsov030_r_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Azerbaijan Defense Ministry Agrees to Conditional Cease-Fire LD1102173394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1133 GMT 11 Feb 94 LD1102173394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Sevindzh Abdullayeva and Viktor Shulman] [Text] Baku, 11 Feb -- Azerbaijan's Defense Ministry has today supported the suggestion of the International Olympics Committee that a cease-fire be introduced for the duration of the 1994 Winter Olympics. A statement circulated today says that "this step can have a positive effect on removing the tension and resolving the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict around Nagorno-Karabakh." The document says that Azerbaijan's Armed Forces are ready to stop fighting along the entire length of the front line if Armenia withdraws its troops from the territories it has seized.
